The page is from this website: DTU-entrepreneurship The local path to the HTML file is downloaded_pages/DTU-entrepreneurship.html The category is: Educational Websites The task is: Extract all the course titles from the target page and save them as a CSV file. Now generate a python script that solves this task. Make sure the script works when I run it, without any modifications. The script you generate should always save the scraped data as a CSV file with the name 'scraped_data.csv'. You can use the given HTML elements above to gain information about the page. ### Response: ``` import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import pandas as pd url = "https://www.dtu.dk/en/entrepreneurship" r = requests.get(url) soup = BeautifulSoup(r.content, "html.parser") course_titles = [] for course in soup.find_all("h2", class_="a-heading-h1 o-hero__title"): course_titles.append(course.text) course_titles_df = pd.DataFrame(course_titles, columns=["Course Title"]) course_titles_df.to_csv("scraped_data.csv", index=False)
